“Rocky Mountain Way” by Joe Walsh, Dave Grohl and Roy Orbison 3, VetsAid 2022

Joe Walsh invited his 6 year old godson Roy Orbison 3 on stage for the finale of his sixth annual VetsAid charity concert at “Ohio’s Nationwide Arena,” Columbus, Ohio, November 13th, 2022. 

Roy 3 played Walsh’s “Rocky Mountain Way” with his godfather on vocals and lead guitar, Dave Grohl on drums, Nathan East on bass, and “The Breeders” as backup singers.

“Top 10 Singers of All Time” by Roy Orbison Jr

Yes, this list is subjective, arguable and controversial. I have tried to use the same criteria that I imagine Rolling Stone Magazine tried to use: singing, popularity, influence, style, genre, time period, vocal inovation, hit songs, chart position, sales, songwriting for the voice.

I understand that art cannot be judged in a list. Still Rolling Stone did it, so here is my humble attempt to correct their mistakes.

(I purposefully did not place my father, Roy Orbison, at the top of the list although he is my personal favorite singer.)

Here goes:

	1.	Elvis
	2.	Frank Sinatra
	3.	Michael Jackson
	4.	Paul McCartney
	5.	Louis Armstrong
	6.	Roy Orbison
	7.	Whitney Houston
	8.	Hank Williams
	9.	Bob Marley 
  10.  Dolly Parton

In October I decided to sign up for Los Angeles Marathon! It’s this Sunday! Like everyone taking marathon seriously I’ve read books and read so much online on how to do this. Spent so many hours running and walking this past 6 months learnt a lot. I’m still not sure I will make it. Today is my rest day and tomorrow morning I have to wake up at 4 and make my way down to dodger stadium. To me, waking up and showing up that early seems harder than the actual run.. think I’ll make it there and think I’ll make it?! 

My pirates are cheering for me!

Made it to the starting line! 

#lamarathon #lamarathon2023

Mile 14 was still looking good. Felt I could go on forever

Then at 16.5 it gets very hard to continue.

I made some mistakes.

By mile 16 they were making us run on sidewalks and cross sideways across streets.

And then at Mile 18 it started raining . . .

I quit at Mile 19.

Next year I’ll get it!

Thank you for your support!!! 🙏🏼

#lamarathon #lamarathon2023

Los Angeles Marathon yesterday was an amazing experience!

I walked & ran through lots of different neighborhoods. Saw so many smiling faces sitting on their porches watching us. Great humanity in the city that day.

Makes me wish everyday was #LosAngelesMarathon day in LA!

Look what was on tv during the LA Marathon 2023 -

“Go Daddy Roy Orbison Jr! Love You! Roy 3, Bo & Love!”

Thank You Boys ☀️

“Roy Orbison Jr and his wife Asa are expecting another baby boy together, a rep for the couple confirms exclusively to PEOPLE. This is the fourth baby for the couple, who is already parents to sons Roy Orbison III, 7, Bo, 5, and Love, 17 months.

"My dad Roy Orbison had five boys so I think this runs in the family," Orbison Jr. tells PEOPLE. "We weren't super surprised when we found out we were expecting one more boy, but we are very excited!"

"My last pregnancy, I still had hopes and thoughts of maybe one more," Asa reveals. "We joke and say, 'Three wasn't quite enough and four is too many.'"

"We are very lucky to fill up our home and lives with these amazing kids and both Roy and I take a lot of pride and honor in devoting ourselves to raising them the best we can."”

Official music video for “Blue Bayou” by Asa Orbison. With behind-the-scenes footage from the recording of the song , which is the first single from her album of the same name , “Blue Bayou”. Produced by Roy Orbison Jr, who rearranged the hit song written by his father, Roy Orbison, in 1963 (and famously covered by Linda Ronstadt in 1977), Roy Jr’s wife Asa gives Blue Bayou an updated jazzy feel with a Scandinavian touch.

Accompanied by Mr Harmonica, Charlie McCoy who played on the original “Blue Bayou” and part-time Traveling Wilbury, Jim Horn, on saxophone and a stellar jazz quartet lead by Roy Orbison Jr on guitar. Bruce Dudley on piano, James Ferguson on bass and Josh Hunt on drums. Featuring special guest and family friend, Ana Cristina Cash, on background vocals. 

Recorded at Roy Orbison Jr’s “Pretty Woman Studio”, Nashville A Team member Wayne Moss’ “Cinderella Studio” and Jack Clement’s “The Cowboy Arms Hotel And Recording Spa”. 

Engineered by Luke Chalk and mixed by Cameron Davidson (husband of Emily Orbison, Roy’s granddaughter). 

Mastered by Richard Dodd who worked on Roy Orbison’s “You Got It” and The Traveling Wilburys.

“Blue Bayou” is available on Spotify!

A Special Reunion!

James Burton, Linda Thompson and I spent the whole day yesterday talking about Elvis Presley, Roy Orbison, Hee Haw and alot of amazing stories and memories.

I have known Linda since I was 6 or 7 years old. I met James in 1987 at the “Black and White Night” concert when he and Elvis’ TCB band joined my Dad for that unbelievably good concert with Bruce Springsteen.

They are both amazingly talented, hard-working superstars that are role models for me and millions of their fans throughout their 50+ & 70+ year careers.

The “Elvis” energy was tangible in the room with them. ⚡️

I learned more about what a great and special man Elvis Presley was from listening to them than my entire lifetime reading books and watching documentaries.

Thank you Linda & James

I love you both ❤️❤️
